Package com.datastructures.interfaces

Interface DictionaryInterface<K,​V>

All Known Implementing Classes:
SortedArrayDictionary, UnsortedArrayDictionary
public interface DictionaryInterface<K,​V>

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    V add​(K key, V value)
    Adds a new entry to this dictionary.
    void clear()
    Removes all entries from this dictionary.

    Sees whether a specific entry is in this dictionary.

  • Method Details

    • add

      V add​(K key, V value)
      Adds a new entry to this dictionary. If the given search key already exists in the dictionary, replaces the corresponding value.
      Parameters:
      key - An object search key of the new entry.
      value - An object associated with the search key.
      Returns:
      Either null if the new entry was added to the dictionary or the value that was associated with key if that was replaced.

    • remove

      V remove​(K key)
      Removes a specific entry from this dictionary.
      Parameters:
      key - An object search key of the entry to be removed.
      Returns:
      Either the value that was associated with the search key or null if no such object exists.

    • getValue

      V getValue​(K key)
      Retrieves from this dictionary the value associated with a given search key.
      Parameters:
      key - An object search key of the entry to be retrieved.
      Returns:
      Either the value that is associated with the search key or null if no such object exists.

    • contains

      boolean contains​(K key)
      Sees whether a specific entry is in this dictionary.
      Parameters:
      key - An object search key of the desired entry.
      Returns:
      True if key is associated with an entry in the dictionary.

    • getKeyIterator

      java.util.Iterator<K> getKeyIterator()
      Creates an iterator that traverses all search keys in this dictionary.
      Returns:
      An iterator that provides sequential access to the search keys in the dictionary.

    • getValueIterator

      java.util.Iterator<V> getValueIterator()
      Creates an iterator that traverses all values in this dictionary.
      Returns:
      An iterator that provides sequential access to the values in this dictionary.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Sees whether this dictionary is empty.
      Returns:
      True if the dictionary is empty.

    • getSize

      int getSize()
      Gets the size of this dictionary.
      Returns:
      The number of entries (key-value pairs) currently in the dictionary.

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all entries from this dictionary.
